OL,3,CHantavirus cruise ship still days away
OL,4,Cfrom docking in Tenerife
OL,6,FA cruise ship at the centre of a
OL,7,Fhantavirus outbreak is still days away
OL,8,Ffrom docking, as global health
OL,9,Fofficials said two Britons who were
OL,10,Fmedically evacuated are improving.
OL,12,FA British passenger, understood to be
OL,13,Fa 69-year-old man, was taken to South
OL,14,FAfrica on April 27 and is receiving
OL,15,Fcare at a private health facility in
OL,16,FSandton, Johannesburg.
OL,18,FAnother Briton, Martin Anstee, 56, was
OL,19,Ftaken off the MV Hondius on Wednesday
OL,20,Fand flown to the Netherlands to
OL,21,Freceive specialist medical care.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
